# Form UI Standards

Use consistent spacing and border radius for form category components to prevent layout and visual drift from mockups.

## Rules

1. **Border radius:** Form cards, inputs, and form-related containers use `rounded-[6px]` (6px).
2. **Spacing between form fields:** Use `gap-2` or `space-y-2` (8px) between form fields within a card or section.
3. **Submit button loading:** Use `Button` from `@sol/ui` with **`isLoading={...}`** — it overlays `Spinner` on the label (label stays in layout, visually hidden while loading). Do not hand-roll spinner + `invisible` spans unless `asChild` forces it. Do not swap the label to "Saving…".

## Tailwind Usage

```tsx
// Form card container
<Card className="rounded-[6px]">
  <CardContent className="space-y-2">
    {/* 8px between fields */}
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

```tsx
// Grid of form fields
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
  {/* 8px gap between items */}
</div>
```

```tsx
// Vertical stack of fields
<div className="space-y-2">
  <FormField />
  <FormField />
</div>
```

### Submit button with loading (`isLoading`)

```tsx
<Button type="submit" form={formId} disabled={disableAll} isLoading={isPending}>
  {submitButtonLabel}
</Button>
```

`isLoading` sets `aria-busy`, disables the button, and applies `relative` + spinner overlay internally. **`isLoading` is ignored when `asChild` is true** (Radix `Slot`); use manual overlay only in that rare case.

## Values

| Property | Value | Tailwind |
|----------|-------|----------|
| Border radius | 6px | `rounded-[6px]` |
| Spacing between fields | 8px | `gap-2` or `space-y-2` |
